"reviewcomment":"Three words:<br><br>Black. Truffle. Carbonara. <br><br>It was Christmas Eve Day and every spot we had tried to go to in Rome was closed. Low and behold though, like a glorious manger in Bethlehem, Da Francesco was open! <br><br>This is a small neighbourhood friendly spot, made up of both tourists and regulars. We were sat at once and menus placed down, but it didn&#39;t matter, I knew just what I wanted. Carbonara with a black truffle sauce. Oh yes. And it lived up to just what I wanted. The sauce and overwhelming in the best kind of way (if you don&#39;t like black truffle, stay away, as this is filled with it). The pasta hot, fresh, creamy, so good. Just what I wanted. I still wanted it today. <br><br>I wanted a glass of wine but it turns out they only do bottles (and small ones for those drinking by themselves). Oh well, if you insist. <br><br>We watched it get crowded so you may have to come early or wait, but the wait is worth it. Travel through Rome but make sure to place this spot on your must see with the Colosseum and the Vatican. You will regret if if you do not.",
