"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"Adore this place! Love this place! Go to this place--especially on Thursday night when there is live jazz, which (when good) easily captures my heart. It&#39;s such a sweet little spot, and even with recommendations from my Roman friends, I&#39;m more pleased with stumbling on this place than with the places the Romans have recommended.<br><br>The bartender and staff are incredibly friendly and hospitable (by far the best I&#39;ve seen in my visit to Rome, but even better than France and NL, where I live or have lived). They are kind, generous, thoughtful--Treating me (a foreigner) just like the others despite my lack of Italian.<br><br>The food is tasty and flavorful. But don&#39;t go just for the food.  Go for the adorable atmosphere. It&#39;s like having friends over to your living room. It&#39;s unpretentious, yet classy. It&#39;s cool and comfortable.  The clientele are mostly late 20/30/40 somethings, and on Thursday night, obviously appreciate jazz. I could stay here all night--(if I had jazz loving friends, but not sure it would be hard to convince with this atmosphere)! But even solo, this is a cool place to be (trying it out tonight!) <br><br>The neighborhood might have some tourist traps scattered about, but this isn&#39;t one of them! I haven&#39;t spotted any other non-Italian speakers and there&#39;s no one heckling you to come in (very good sign!).  <br><br>They have small plates of cold or hot dishes. More like little samplers, which is nice if you&#39;d like to try out a few different dishes. I had the parmigiana and tortino chocolate for dessert (both little plates) but wish I had room for more!  They also have a cocktail menu boasting all the classics.<br><br>If you know a bit of Italian (or can at least understand the written language), ask for the Italian menu.  Otherwise, you&#39;re missing out on some Roman or Italian specialties that are otherwise a mystery when written in English. <br><br>I especially love their antique singer sewing machine DJ table!<br><br>I had a list of other jazz spots and restaurant recommendations for this evening and whatever they are like, I don&#39;t care. I have stumbled upon the sweet spot. And you should too. Get here on Thursday night. You&#39;ll love it!",
