"ogimage":"http://s3-media1.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/Rlj8TpW37tRF-TYszJxjcQ/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"Husband and I came here after seeing Anthony Bourdain eat here on the Layover.  Again, Anthony did not let us down.  <br><br>We started with the cured meat plate.  It wasn&#39;t the most impressive spread, but enjoyable nonetheless.  I ordered the gnocchi with pork cheek and my husband got the veal and mashed potatoes.  We split a side of chicory.  The gnocchi was the best I have ever had.  The gnocchi were larger in size than what I am used to, with an amazing, soft texture.  Husbands veal was very good as were the mashed potatoes.  The chicory was fantastic!  Husband and I feel in love with chicory while in Italy.  For dessert we split the tiramasu.  I honestly don&#39;t remember how good the tiramasu was.  By the time dessert came out I had the better part of a bottle of vino bianco in me.<br><br>When/if I come back to Rome, I&#39;ll definitely come back to Sora Lella.  This was the best meal we had in Rome.  It was the best meal of our honeymoon, before we ate at Kofein in Prague.",
