"ogimage":"http://s3-media1.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/ghafrZDxaMZLNztreZuRKg/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"A true Roman restaurant in an area that is saturated by tourist traps. The food is wonderful: definitely order off the Specials list. The burrata ravioli is extremely addictive. Pasta is made in house and is ready in 5 minutes - just like it should be. Carbonara is a must-eat as well: when simple dishes are done well, there is no substitute. <br>Claudia is the daughter of the chef, and runs the front of the house (which consists of her mother, brother, and boyfriend) superbly. She is kind, intuitive, and knows a ton about food. Speaks flawless English as well, and never makes you feel as an outsider, which is a can make a visit to a foreign city just so much better. <br>The place is packed consistently, so I would suggest calling ahead. Have a nice Roman lunch at 2PM or dinner at 10. <br>Overall, an extremely satisfying experience, whether you are a local or passing through the Eternal City.",
