"reviewcomment":"Kyu L&#39;s &#34;mak[ing] weird noises in the corner&#34; brought us here. THANK YOU KYU. BEST PIZZA IN MY LIFE. Puts everything else to shame.<br><br>The food is worth 4.7, just shy of 5 because of the poor dessert. <br>UPDATE: I&#39;ll raise them to 5. They deserve it. <br>dessert - don&#39;t bother .<br><br>Service 4.5<br><br>Pizza Tartufo (pomodoro, bufala, porcini, salsiccia senese e salsa tartufata) Absolutely stunning. Should have ordered 3 of them. SERIOUSLY. If this is the only thing you get, you will be a happy person.<br><br>Patanegra, was good.<br>Noci (blue cheese and honey, walnuts) a little underwhelming.<br>Porcini e patate was the least good of them all, still darn good though.<br><br>Pastas ordered were the <br>Tagliolini con astice (lobster) - lip smacking delicious,<br>Ravioli ripieni di burrata, really good but shy of the lobster.<br><br>Mains seabass - standard salt crusted style.<br><br>Sfoglia croccante (pastry tart for with Chantilly cream) was poor. Desserts are not really their speciality; the waitress recommended this one.<br><br>You should go out of your way to get here. Especially if you&#39;re a tourist. No offence to Americans, don&#39;t just be a sight-seer and eat sandwiches and boxed lunches all the time and fail to appreciate the delicious cuisine this country has to offer.",
