"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"Our third time in Rome, my husband and I would only be there for one night and wanted to have a relaxed, romantic evening. We were staying in our favourite place, right beside the Pantheon, and wanted to eat somewhere close by. We thought it might be a bit challenging as it&#39;s such a touristy area, but we were lucky to find this gem. It&#39;s just a few minutes walk from the Pantheon, tucked away on a side street on the minuscule Piazza delle Coppelle. <br><br>We arrived very shortly after they opened and were lucky to get a table outside. It was a gorgeous evening. There are only a handful of outdoor tables and they are very close together. I walked through the restaurant later and it was a lot more spacious than I expected. Gorgeous, too. Don&#39;t hesitate to dine in the restaurant if outside isn&#39;t available.<br><br>They have a great wine list and their own sommelier, but we settled on a half bottle of house red for 9EUR. I didn&#39;t write down what we had, but looking at the menu now I&#39;m sure we had the Rigatoni all&#39;Amatricianella (Rigatoni Amatricianella style with cherry tomatoes, Norcia Bacon flambé with Cognac) and the Rigatoni amatriciana con guanciale di norcia (Rigatoni Amatriciana style with Norcia bacon and spicy tomato sauce). Both dishes were fresh down to the very last ingredient and oh so delicious. I wish I wouldn&#39;t have been so full, because I would have loved to order more food here!<br><br>Service was fairly prompt and friendly while still being professional. I&#39;m looking forward to dining here again the next time I am in Roma.",
