"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"Tripa &amp; Caccio!!<br><br>Yumm yummm. I love this place and their beautiful outdoor seating. It is not right in the middle of all the crazy busy things. It&#39;s almost kind of hidden but it&#39;s easy to find. You can sit inside and outside but definitely choose outside for lunch. You can gaze into the buildings , narrow little cobble stone streets and people watch as you dine on their delicious offering.<br><br>Who gets steak in Rome? You should! Romans are known for their love of meat. Meat, offals and all things simple and cheesy. Baccala too but they didn&#39;t have it here.<br><br>Steak- great! Comes with a side of simple salad. <br>Caccio e pepe - this version of caccio e pepe is a wet one. Its wet and creamy. I prefer the dry style. But it is still tasty. They use a big pasta which is so divine.<br>Tripa - classic roman dish. Tripe in tomato sauce. Spicy too! Yummmm<br>Proscuitto and dolce! Yumm yumm.<br><br>Overall, it was a laid back lunch on a very hot summer day in Rome. Make sure you call ahead because you will need a reservation. This place is always packed! Service is efficient. If you speak italian, it gets even better :) Food will put you in a food coma. What&#39;s not to love??!",
