"ogimage":"http://s3-media4.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/hJ9fFMw1x49As1AYyIXnZA/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"We went here for dinner twice while in Rome for a week. It&#39;s in a very typical Roman residential neighborhood of Monteverde. Not touristy at all, but more for the local folks in the hood. They make an awesome pizza - not round  but more oval in shape - that is made with an &#34;antique crushed dough pizza&#34; method which is apparently more than 2,000 years old and was practiced here in ancient Rome that long ago. The crust is very light and fluffy. The toppings are great in variety. <br><br>The menu is fairly simple and consists mostly of appetizers, salads and pasta and  pizza. I&#39;d recommend people try the &#34;ancient pizza&#34; because you will never ever eat this kind of pizza anywhere else, its very unique as tastes great. One pizza plate is more than enough for one person and can be easily shared between two for not very much money. They also have great wines and desserts. Their prices are very reasonable and the host and wait staff are very helpful (spoke English) and welcoming. You will have a great dinner here.",
