"categorystrlist":"Bakeries,Juice Bars & Smoothies,Italian",
"ogimage":"http://s3-media4.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/0mvjOn7fwBmc4eo8RRExcg/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"Went in for coffee at the bar, came back 3 more times for their fantastic pasta!<br>I guess the first sentence in itself already says everything you need to know in order for you to give this place a try...<br><br>A super charming, modern-chic small café/&#34;bistro&#34;, this place has exceptionally good pasta, great coffee at really fair prices and a great lunch special that&#39;s worth trying out.<br>After coming in to get a EUR 1 espresso at the bar we had a look at the menu and took some recommendations from the bar tender to try the house-made carbonara pasta. And boy was it fantastic (this rating is nothing short of a miracle, because I am usually not even a fan of carbonara sauce). <br>But let me start from the top. The coffee this place serves was some of the best we have had in Rome, with flavors not quite as &#34;burnt&#34; as in other places and therefore extremely smooth, balanced and tasty. <br>After taking a look at the menu and discovering their EUR 10 lunch menu (featuring 1 &#34;piece&#34; of bruschetta, your choice of pasta, 0.5l of water and a coffee afterwards) we decided to try it out. <br>The pasta was without a doubt the best pasta I have ever eaten anywhere and I am a true pastafan, so this is not a compliment I would give out easily.  <br>We came back 3 more times to have more of their delicious carbonara and just-as-delicious amatriciana sauce. To-die-for (both, the sauces as well as the pasta) <br><br>Definitely give this charming place with its nice decor, soothing music and awesome food a try if you&#39;re passing throughout one of the cutest streets in Rome (the street itself and it&#39;s artsy shops are worth a visit regardless if you&#39;re hungry or not). <br><br>Fantastico! Will definitely be back next time I&#39;m in Rome!!!",
