"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"My bf &amp; I went spent 9 days in Rome during December 2012 and this was our first dining experience in Italy. The food here is fantastic and the service was friendly. It is hidden in a narrow street so it may be difficult to find. I recommend asking a local for directions which is what we did.<br><br>We loved the pasta dishes in cream sauce here - most notable would be the vodka sauce, carbonara &amp; prosciutto/peas/broccoli combo. The thin crust pizzas cooked in a wood oven here is excellent. Crust is chewy and plenty of toppings. Our favorite was the prosciutto &amp; fungi pizza. Pizza&#39;s are huge so we had to take leftovers back to the hotel with us. Their panna cotta is to not be missed! Perfect texture and is served with a drizzle of raspberry sauce. <br><br>Overall, we loved this place so much that we came back 3 times! Very affordable (10-12 euros per dish) and authentic. I highly recommend this place and you won&#39;t be disappointed. Will stop by here again if we make it back to Rome in the future. It&#39;s that good!",
