"reviewcomment":"This is my favorite place in Roma.  Granted I have only been to Rome twice, but both times, I have eaten here.  I will make it a tradition.  When I had been in Rome last summer, we asked the cab driver for a more homespun restaurant.  He delivered.  it is very authentic and not pretenses and yet the food is fresh and not so pricy!  And while I wouldn&#39;t say it is the highest quality fo0od, it is really good, and the environment is wonderful.  I actually walked past it this time, and then did backsteps like you see in a cartoon.  I was like, I AM SO EATING HERE AGAIN!<br>The neighborhood is Fantastic and Alive (Trastavere).  I was just there this month (November) and ate outside regardless of the slight coolness.  It was a Friday night, I dined alone.  My friend&#39;s flight was canceled due to the Hurricane in the US.  However, with the extremely animated waiter, I never felt alone.  He was flying through the space, taking orders, delivering food, moving chairs and tables.  But he would take the time to sit with you and take your order. <br>When I had been in Rome last summer, we asked the cab driver for a more homespun restaurant.  He delivered.  it is very authentic and not pretenses and yet the food is fresh and not so pricy!  <br>The wine is local, the place is crowded with families and groups of 10 or more trying to get a table at 10pm.  LOVE IT!",
