"categorystrlist":"Japanese",
"ogimage":"http://s3-media1.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/0Ir46uU2-Xy8oP5Tt-5F8Q/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"My husband and I are from Portland, Oregon and we love sushi, I mean LOVE sushi. So after eating a ton (literally) of pasta we wanted some comfort food from home. We Yelp searched and found Taki and thank god that we did!! It was the best dining experience that we have had in Italy after being here for 4 days. The waitress was extremely friendly and helpful with the menu that was in Japanese and Italian. She spoke English so we were able to ask for some of our favorite sushi rolls and make some changes. The sushi was fantastic! Extremely fresh and well made!! We HIGHLY recommend this place to anyone who loves sushi and if you are wanting some variety in Rome. Just a heads up it is a little pricy, but since sushi is a comfort food and everyone was so welcoming it was a wonderful slice if home for us and worth every penny. Also, we did need to ask for wasabi but they brought us a great mound of it and they had some interesting Italian style options if you are adventurous. And the cheesecake dessert was heavenly. I would add more stars if I could, thank you Taki for a memorable night! :)",
