"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"After more than a week of non stop pasta and pizza in Italy, my friend and I decided that we should see what other types of foods Rome has to offer. After looking all over we saw that there was an Indian restaurant that had pretty good reviews. Jaipur for dinner it was!<br><br>To begin our meal we got an order of vegetable samosas that were absolutely delicious. It may be the best thing I had at the restaurant. They were perfectly cooked and scrumptious. We also got an order of naan that was great too. For my meal I decided on getting the Jaipuru Murgh. It could have been better, but it was still pretty good. My friend got the chicken Tikka Masala, which she said was great. I tried a bite of it, and I thought the Tikka Masala was better than my meal. For dessert I got the Kulfi which is an almond and pistachio ice cream which was amazing. I loved it! My friend got the Nariyal ki Kulfi which was a coconut ice cream. My friend claimed it was the best coconut ice cream she had on the trip.<br><br>Overall, Jaipur was very tasty! I was a much appreciated and much needed change from the usual Italian fare offered throughout Rome.",
