"reviewcomment":"We got 2 sandiwches/pannini&#39;s  for a total of 4.60 Euro at the Deli section of the store.  Really cheap for lunch if you ask me and tons of locals and tourists go to this shop.  They are very friendly and even take credit card.  They also sell a European to US (3 prong) adapter for laptops if you need it.  They eat their panini&#39;s cold, which in the states, we usually eat ours toasted/heated.  I got used to it.  I would definitely come here again.<br><br>Had their caffe espresso and caffe macchiato at their sit down location just next door to their deli shop.  Great place to sit on the side of the street and just to people watch and to watch the street vendors trying to sell their &#34;gooey/gel&#34; toy. Their espresso was VERY strong and bitter.  I like mine to be a little sweeter so I added a whole pack of sugar into it.  The macchiato was nice and creamy.",
