"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"One thing that has always struck me about Rome is the lack of choice when it comes to international cuisine. The city is unsurprisingly full of Italian restaurants, but if you want something a bit different, then it can be tricky to find somewhere good.<br><br> Cue my surprise and pleasure when I discovered Maharajah, tucked away down a fairly quiet road in Rome. Specialising in tandoori cuisine, but also with a good selection of curries, the quality and presentation of the food is very good, combining with a very pleasant atmosphere (although, better on the ground floor than in the basement) and excellent service. Mains are about EUR10-EUR14, rice is cheekily priced at EUR6, and naan EUR3. They also do some very reasonable set menus around the EUR25 mark.<br><br> As a Brit who misses his curry, I&#39;ve been dying to find somewhere good in Rome, and Maharaja hits the spot nicely.",
